findings.title: Out of gas
findings.description: The functions includeInReward(), _getCurrentSupply(), and amnestySniper() use loops that can cause an OUT_OF_GAS exception if the arrays' length is too big.

findings.title: Return value of low-level calls not used
findings.description: The return values of low-level calls are not being utilized.

findings.title: Failure condition of 'send' ignored. Consider using 'transfer' instead
findings.description: The function uses 'send' without checking its return value, which can lead to unexpected behavior if the call fails.

findings.title: Owner privileges (In the period when the owner is not renounced)
findings.description: The contract owner has excessive privileges during a certain period, including initializing the contract, opening trading, changing various parameters, and performing other actions.
